            "raw_content": "Senate President Bill Ferguson (D-Baltimore City) gives remarks Tuesday during bill signing ceremony in Annapolis, as Gov. Wes Moore (D) listens. (Photo by William J. Ford/Maryland Matters)    Less than a week after Gov. Wes Moore (D) released a list of Democratic endorsements that snubbed Senate President Bill Ferguson (D-Baltimore City), the political arm of the prominent immigrant rights and advocacy group this week endorsed Ferguson as &#8220;the right leader moving forward.&#8221; \n It was one of  143 endorsements  released Wednesday by CASA in Action for Maryland congressional, state and county races. It is the political arm of We Are CASA, the immigrant rights organization that heavily involved in passage of bills in this year&#8217;s legislative session that expanded protections against immigration detention and deportation. \n The list included several Democrats who were not endorsed by Moore, but Ferguson was the most noteworthy. \n “Our board looked at the totality of his [Ferguson&#8217;s] tenure in the Senate, we concluded he is the right leader moving forward,” Cathyrn Jackson, policy director for CASA in Action, said Thursday. \n “Since he became Senate president, Maryland has passed legislation that has made a real difference in people’s lives,&#8221; Jackson said. &#8220;This year we were able to get the Data Privacy Act, Community Trust Act [and] 287(g) passed. These are all victories that ultimately Bill Ferguson got on board with and delivered.” \n While it wa",
